
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-xu-sfc-using-mpls-spring-06.txt'>
    <title>"Service Function Chaining Using MPLS-SPRING", Xiaohu Xu, Himanshu Shah, Luis Contreras, daniel.bernier@bell.ca</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-xu-sfc-using-mpls-spring-06.txt</link>
    <description>Source Packet Routing in Networking (SPRING) WG specifies a special source routing mechanism.  Such source routing mechanism can be leveraged to realize the service path layer functionality of the service function chaining (i.e, steering traffic through a particular service function path) by encoding the service function path or the service function chain information as the explicit path information. This document describes how to leverage the MPLS-based source routing mechanism as developed by the SPRING WG to realize the service path layer functionality of the service function chaining.</description>
    <dc:date>2016-07-03T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
